The paper proposes a novel approach for unsupervised clustering using a Variational Autoencoder (VAE) framework, which is a popular topic in the machine learning community and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed approach is demonstrated on the MNIST dataset, which is a well-known computer vision dataset, suggesting that the paper may also fall under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of Gaussian mixture models, which is a common technique in unsupervised learning and clustering, suggesting that the paper may also fall under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of outlier detection, which is a common topic in neural networks and machine learning, suggesting that the paper may also fall under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper applies the proposed approach to resting-state fMRI connectivity analysis, which is a topic in medical imaging and neuroscience, suggesting that the paper may also fall under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
